Your task is very simple: given two integers A and B, write a program to add these two numbers and output the sum.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer T, the total number of test cases.
Then follow ğ‘‡ lines, each line contains two integers, A and ğµ.

Output Format
For each test case, add A and B and display the sum in a new line.

Sample 1:
Input                          Output
1 2                              3
100 200                         300
10 40                           50


Explanation:
Testcase 1 : 1 + 2 = 3. Hence the first output is 3.
Testcase 2 : 100 + 200 = 300.Hence the second output is 300.

Code:-  

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int t;
    scanf("%d", &t);

    // Loop for each test case
    while (t--) {
        int a, b;

        scanf("%d %d", &a, &b);
        printf("%d\n",a+b);
    }
}
